<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="562" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1303,1400]" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1303,1328]" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small to medium sized 
<taxonomicName box="[541,681,1303,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anthonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[541,681,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Anthonomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<quantity box="[782,919,1304,1328]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" metricValueMax="4.4" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="562" unit="mm" value="3.3" valueMax="4.4" valueMin="2.2">2.2–4.4 mm</quantity>
) similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1045,1185,1303,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anthonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1045,1185,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Anthonomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1192,1243,1304,1327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="562" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Antennal funicle with six segments. Elytra with two transverse bands and pronotum with median longitudinal line formed of dense whitish seta-like scales. Profemora toothed. Tarsi slender, claws with or without teeth. Wings present.
</paragraph>
